body:
Just to explain, if I create a new app with:

```java
public class ManagementInterfaceRoute {

    public void init(@Observes ManagementInterface itf) {
        itf.router().post("/q/test")
                .handler(rc -> {
                    String message = rc.body().asString();
                    rc.response().end("Received: " + message);
                });
    }
}
```

And 2 tests:

```java
@QuarkusTest
class GreetingResourceTest {

    @Test
    void testPostOnManagementInterface() {
        given()
                .body("Hello Management Interface")
                .when().post("http://localhost:9001/q/test")
                .then()
                .statusCode(200)
                .body(is("Received: Hello Management Interface"));
    }

    @Test
    void testPostOnManagementInterfaceAsForm() {
        given()
                .formParam("name", "John Doe")
                .when().post("http://localhost:9001/q/test")
                .then()
                .statusCode(200)
                .body(is("Received: name=John%20Doe"));
    }

}
```

It passes.... 

My config only contains: `quarkus.management.enabled=true`
